#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:85-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_viewer.htm+html.body.h2:85-1"
msgid "Frames Context Menu"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:86-1
msgid ""
"The context menu for a frame is opened by pressing the <b>APPLICATIONS</b> "
"key. The following options are available from this context menu."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:87-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Frame Properties</b>: Opens a multi page "
"dialog containing General Properties, Validation Rules, Events, and Position "
"information. Refer to <a href=\"frame_properties.htm\">Frame Properties</a> "
"for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:88-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Status</b>: Use this submenu to temporarily "
"disable and enable frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:89-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Move</b>: Use this option to move the frame, "
"right from the keyboard, while receiving spoken feedback. Refer to <a "
"href=\"#_Moving_Frames\">Moving Frames</a> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:90-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Resize</b>: Use this option to resize the "
"frame, right from the keyboard, while receiving spoken feedback. Refer to <a "
"href=\"#_Resizing_Frames\">Resizing Frames</a> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:91-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Events</b>: Opens the Frame Properties "
"dialog to the Events page. Refer to <a "
"href=\"frame_properties.htm#_Events_Properties\">Events Properties</a> for "
"more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:92-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Save Changes</b>: Saves changes to all "
"frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:93-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Frames List</b>: Opens a dialog listing "
"frames currently active, or frames in the current application. Refer to <a "
"href=\"#_Frames_List\">Frames List</a> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:94-1
msgid "<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Delete</b>: Deletes the current frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:95-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Hide Titles</b>: Temporarily hides frame "
"titles."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:96-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Exit Frame Viewer</b>: Exits frame viewer. "
"If changes have been made, but not saved, you are prompted to save changes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:97-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_viewer.htm+html.body.h2:97-1"
msgid "Positioning Frames"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:98-1
msgid ""
"One of the primary factors determining how well a frame will work is how "
"effectively it is positioned. Frames are positioned in the following ways."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:100-1
msgid ""
"When you create a frame,you can size and position the frame to the current "
"control or window, or you can specify the exact location of the top left "
"corner and bottom right corner. For more information, refer to <a "
"href=\"creating_a_frame.htm\">Creating a Frame</a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:101-1
msgid ""
"Open Frame Viewer, press <b>TAB</b> to move to an existing frame, press "
"<b>ALT+ENTER</b> to open the current frame's properties, and press "
"<b>CTRL+TAB</b> to move to the position page. Modify the settings in this "
"dialog to adjust the location and size of the frame. For more information, "
"refer to <a href=\"frame_properties.htm#_Position_Properties\">Position "
"Properties</a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:102-1
msgid ""
"Open Frame Viewer, press <b>TAB</b> to move to an existing frame, and select "
"Move or Resize from the frame's context menu, and use the arrow keys to "
"adjust the position or size of the frame. This method allows you to adjust a "
"frame's size and/or position right within Frame Viewer, and provides spoken "
"feedback as you move or resize a frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:103-1
msgid ""
"Use your mouse to drag a frame by its title bar to a new location, or to "
"drag a border to resize the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:105-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tip</b>: When a person, working visually, "
"uses the mouse to move the mouse pointer over the edge of a frame, the mouse "
"changes shape and becomes a double arrow. If they click and hold the left "
"mouse button they can now drag the edge to change the frame size. When they "
"release the left mouse button, the changed size is retained. They can "
"continue sizing by moving the mouse to another edge and repeating the "
"process. If they simply want to move the frame they would click and hold the "
"left mouse button with the mouse on the title bar of the frame. While the "
"mouse button is held down the person can move the frame freely around the "
"screen. When they release the mouse button, the new position is retained."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:106-1
msgid "Enable Show Window Contents"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:107-1
msgid ""
"If you select the context menu items and use the arrow keys to move or "
"resize a frame, you first need to check the Show Window Contents While "
"Dragging check box in the Effects page of Display Properties. This will "
"ensure you receive the maximum feedback while you are moving or resizing a "
"frame. To do this:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:109-1
msgid "Press the <b>WINDOWS KEY</b> to open the Start Menu."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:110-1
msgid "Select Settings, Control Panel."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:111-1
msgid "Select Display Properties."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:112-1
msgid "Press <b>CTRL+TAB</b> until you are at the Effects page."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:113-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TAB</b> to the Show Window Contents While "
"Dragging check box and press <b>SPACEBAR</b> to check it if it is not "
"already checked."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:115-1
msgid ""
"This ensures you receive spoken feedback as you move or resize a frame. If "
"you do not check this check box, you still receive spoken feedback, but only "
"after completing the operation."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:116-1
msgid "Moving Frames"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:117-1
msgid "To move frames with the arrow keys:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:119-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_viewer.htm+html.body.ol.li:119-1"
msgid "Press <b>INSERT+F2</b>, move to Frame Viewer, and press <b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:120-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TAB</b> to the frame you wish to reposition."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:121-1
msgid "Press the <b>APPLICATIONS</b> key. Then press <b>M</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:122-1
msgid ""
"Press the arrow key corresponding to the direction you wish to move the "
"frame. As you press arrow keys and the frame moves, the distance in pixels "
"is reported."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:123-1
msgid ""
"Press <b>INSERT+DOWN ARROW</b> to hear what text is within the borders of "
"the frame. This should assist you in verifying the frame is positioned where "
"you need it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:124-1
msgid ""
"Press <b>ENTER</b> when the frame is positioned where you want it, or press "
"<b>ESC</b> to cancel the operation."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:126-1
msgid "Resizing Frames"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:127-1
msgid "To resize a frame with the arrow keys:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:129-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_viewer.htm+html.body.ol.li:129-1"
msgid "Press <b>INSERT+F2</b>, move to Frame Viewer, and press <b>ENTER</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:130-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TAB</b> to the frame you wish to resize."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:131-1
msgid "Press the <b>APPLICATIONS</b> key. Then press <b>R</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:132-1
msgid ""
"Press the arrow key corresponding to the border of the frame you wish to "
"move."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:133-1
msgid ""
"Press the arrow key corresponding to the direction you wish to move the "
"selected border."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:135-1
msgid ""
"For example, if you wish to bring the right border of the frame in (to make "
"the frame smaller), first press <b>RIGHT ARROW</b>, then press <b>LEFT "
"ARROW</b> to move the border of the frame. As you press arrow keys and the "
"border moves, the distance in pixels is reported."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:137-1
msgid ""
"Press <b>INSERT+DOWN ARROW</b> to hear what text is within the borders of "
"the frame. This should assist you in verifying the frame is sized as you "
"need it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:138-1
msgid ""
"Press <b>ENTER</b> when the frame border is positioned where you want it, or "
"press <b>ESC</b> to cancel the operation."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:140-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_viewer.htm+html.body.h2:140-1"
msgid "Frame Viewer Toolbox"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:141-1
msgid ""
"Frame Viewer includes a toolbox containing four buttons: Options, Frames "
"List, Help and Close. The Help button opens the Introduction to Frames help "
"topic, and closes Frame Viewer. The close button closes Frame Viewer. The "
"Options and Frames List buttons are explained in the following sections."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:142-1
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:143-1
msgid ""
"Select the Options button to open a context menu containing the following "
"items:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:144-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Create New Frame</b>: This item creates a "
"new frame positioned on and sized to the control or window that was active "
"when Frame Viewer was opened."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:145-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">View Frames List</b>: This item opens the "
"Frames List dialog."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:146-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Save Changes</b>: This item saves changes to "
"all frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:147-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Exit Frame Viewer</b>: This item closes "
"Frame Viewer. If frame settings have been changed, but not saved, you are "
"prompted to save your changes."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:148-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Status</b>: This item opens a submenu from "
"which you can disable all frames and enable them again."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:149-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Hide Titles</b>: This item temporarily hides "
"titles for all frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:150-1
msgid "Frames List"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:151-1
msgid ""
"The Frames list button opens a dialog that lists all frames for the "
"application that was active when Frame Viewer was opened. This list provides "
"an alternate means of working with your frames, and provides access to "
"frames that are inactive. Frame Viewer does not display frames that are "
"inactive, so the Frames List dialog is the only way to access and make "
"modifications to inactive frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:152-1
msgid ""
"An inactive frame has Validation Rules set to check for conditions that are "
"not met at the time Frame Viewer was opened. For example, if a frame is set "
"to be active in the Options dialog within an application, but Frame Viewer "
"is opened from the application's Settings dialog, the frame would be "
"inactive."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:153-1
msgid "The following commands are available from the list of Frames:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.table.tbody.tr.th.p:157-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frame_viewer.htm+html.body.table.tbody.tr.th.p:157-1"
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframe_viewer.htm%2Bhtml.body.table.tbody.tr.th.p:160-1
